\insrsid3810134\charrsid3810134 
\par }\pard\plain \s2\ql \li0\ri0\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel1\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid14312139 \b\i\f1\fs28\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid14312139 Entering Stations
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid14312139 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid14312139 
Entering stations allows you to access the station hanger as well as save your game.
\par 
\par Dock to a non-hostile station and a UniGUI menu will show an \'93Enter Station\'94 option. Mouse click this button to enter the station. You will find yourself inside the station. (Long time EoC players will recognize this as Lucretia\rquote 
s base. But unlike the base, this works for any station.) 
\par 
\par Once inside the station, use the hanger menu to loadout your ship. Or press escape to get to the options screen, where you can save your game, or Load a prior game.
\par 
\par To get back into space, Launch from the hanger menu. You will find yourself back in space, docked to the same station you entered. Any of your wingmen will be returned to where they were when you entered the station.}{\insrsid14312139\charrsid14312139 

\par }\pard\plain \s2\ql \li0\ri0\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel1\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid16400692 \b\i\f1\fs28\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid14312139 Save Anywhere
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid14312139 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid14312139 
Epic allows you to save when you are inside a station, just as the standard EoC game does. It also allows you to save when you are in deep space. 
\par 
\par You must travel at least 1000km away from any station or Lpoint. And there must be no hostile ships near
by. Then open the UniGUI menu and you will have a Save Game button. Press this button to open a save game menu and select a save game slot. Your game will be saved at this point. 
\par 
\par You can load this save game just like a game saved inside the base. But when the game loads, your ship will be returned to this save location. And any wingmen you have will be placed where they were at the moment you saved.
\par }{\insrsid3810134 
\par }{\b\insrsid3810134\charrsid3810134 Limitations}{\b\insrsid3810134 
\par }{\insrsid3810134 EoC was not designed with a save anywhere feature. The information that is saved is very limit
ed. It saves the player ship and player wingmen. But it does not save ship damage or subsystem damage. Those return to healed when the game is restored. This opens a possible exploit for player. You will have to choose to use this feature for convenience,
 or exploit it for healing. It is your game, after all.}{\insrsid3810134\charrsid3810134 
\par }{\insrsid14312139 
\par }{\insrsid3810134 The game does not save current traffic or station damage. If you are chasing some pirates back to their base, do not save! They will not exist when you restart. Instead, finish your chase and only save when the combat is resolved. 

\par 
\par This feature can be a blessing if you use it to save just before you plan to go into combat. It is also good for saving while making long trade journeys that you do not wish to repeat.
\par }{\insrsid3810134\charrsid14312139 
\par }\pard\plain \s2\ql \li0\ri0\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel1\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid16400692 \b\i\f1\fs28\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid16400692 Ship to Ship Communication
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid16400692 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid16400692 Epic suppo
rts direct ship to ship communication with some Nonplayer ships. These ships are typically mercenaries for hire or ships selling illegal goods and services.
\par 
\par Most of these ships are marked on your contact list with a pale blue color. More illegal ships tend to hide, waiting for contact. Target a possible ship and press Ctrl K to start communications. If the ship is open to contact, a dialog will appear. Follow
 the prompts to purchase goods and services.}{\insrsid16400692\charrsid16400692 
\par }\pard\plain \s2\ql \li0\ri0\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel1\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid16400692 \b\i\f1\fs28\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid16400692 Hiring Wingmen
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid11481553 
There are ships for hire throughout the Middle States. These ships are typically marked with a pale blue color. Use the ship to ship communication feature to open a dialog with a prospective wingman.
\par }\pard\plain \s3\ql \li0\ri0\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel2\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid11481553 \b\f1\fs26\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid11481553 Hiring Fee
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid11481553 
Every ship has a hiring fee. The fee increases with the size and firepower of the ship. The hiring fee makes it important to budget c}{\insrsid14312139 
arefully. Constant hiring and firing of ships can be much more expensive than just paying the ships upkeep.}{\insrsid11481553 
\par }\pard\plain \s3\ql \li0\ri0\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel2\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid11481553 \b\f1\fs26\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid11481553 Upkeep Fee
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid11481553 Every ship charges a dai}{\insrsid9773136 ly upkeep fee for salary, parts, }{\insrsid11481553 
and repairs. These fees are taken out of your cash accounts. If you cannot pay the upkeep, your wingmen will desert. Each type of ship has a cost. The larger the ship, the larger the fee. 
\par }\pard\plain \s3\ql \li0\ri0\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel2\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid9773136 \b\f1\fs26\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid9773136 Jump Fuel
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid9773136 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid9773136 
Each ship uses fuel when it capsule jumps to a new star system. The larger the ship, the more fuel it uses. Fuel is billed at 1 credit per unit of fuel used. You can see the fuel cost of jumping your ship in the Wingman Status GUI. Fuel is refilled automa
tically every day when upkeep costs are calculated (in future releases, you will need to refill the ships yourself). If you cannot pay to refuel a ship, it will desert.}{\insrsid9773136\charrsid9773136 
\par }\pard\plain \s3\ql \li0\ri0\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel2\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid11481553 \b\f1\fs26\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid11481553 Desertion}{
\insrsid11481553\charrsid11481553 
