\insrsid2165678 
\par 
\par }{\b\insrsid2165678\charrsid2165678 Dock All
\par }{\insrsid3810134 If you order a group to collect all player pods, they will find all nearby pods that belong to your }{\insrsid2165678 faction and dock those pods to your freighters and utility ships}{\insrsid3810134 . }{\insrsid16400692 
The pods will pilot themselves into docking position. This is much faster and easier than trying to move a huge freighter to dock to a tiny pod.
\par 
\par }{\insrsid3810134 To dock other kinds of ships, use the Dock command to force a docking. The Dock command can also be used to force a wingman to dock with cargo pods that do not belong to you.
\par }{\insrsid16400692 
\par }{\b\insrsid16400692\charrsid16400692 Undock All}{\b\insrsid3810134\charrsid16400692 
\par }{\insrsid3810134 If you order a group to undock all pods, they will drop all pods where they are.}{\insrsid2165678  It can be helpful to move each cargo ship to a unique group, if you want just one ship to drop pods.}{\insrsid3810134 
\par 
\par }{\b\insrsid16400692\charrsid16400692 Dock Pod
\par }{\insrsid2165678 You can use the Dock Pod command to load just one pod. Target the pod, then select the group to load the pod, then cargo commands, then Dock Pod. The targeted pod will be loaded onto a freighter with an empty cargo dock.
